I am now offering 30 minute private core sessions in person and online. Come join the Wolffpack and let’s work!

February 23rd 2016 I was robbed and kidnapped at gunpoint. Today’s marks 7 years since the horrific incident. Sports illustrated wrote a story in first person about it. Click the link in my bio to read it. Its one of the craziest stories you will ever hear. If you know me personally you know that I'm a genuine soul and I don't deserve anything that happened to me that night. I'm good to everybody and one of the most respectful people you will ever meet. I love all. This is just part of testimony. Everything happens for a reason. I'm alive today to tell it, give awareness, and to tell you that God is real! It happened to me. I survived it through prayer. I mean literally praying to God every second that all 5 guys had me tied up at gunpoint and I was zip tied. At first I thought that I was by myself but then called his name and he spoke by saying "I am with you" and I literally felt his presence. I felt a since of peace. If it wasn't for him I'd be dead. That wasn't his calling for my life though. He has a plan for me and he has a plan for you. I'm truly thankful and blessed to be here today. God is good all the time. This situation has made my faith unbreakable and I don't regret going through it. Thankful to see another day. All glory to God 🙌🏾

Regardless of how I felt physically I was ready mentally and spiritually. I knew he wouldn’t fail me! He never has and he’s not going to! 

Always remember God is only one prayer away. Just call his name and he will be by your side 🙏🏾

BIG ANNOUNCEMENT 🔈 

After months of studying, getting my business licenses, accounts, training complete I can officially let you know I am a licensed Life Insurance Broker.

God led me to the confirmation that I myself needed to get life insurance especially with my goal to leave a legacy to my family and daughter… after learning about the benefits of having a life insurance account I thought I absolutely need everyone around me to have one for themselves and the only reason why anyone doesn’t is because they aren’t educated on it! Life insurance is: 

1.) WAY more than just death insurance. Avoid having a go fund me up for when you will one day pass away especially if unexpectedly. 

2.) Cash Value -Cash value is a savings component typically included in permanent life insurance policies. Depending on your particular policy, the cash value can grow at a fixed or variable interest rate over time up to 10% to 12% monthly. You can borrow against your policy's cash value in the form of a life insurance loan.

3.) Take your money out TAX FREE! This is why they call Life insurance the “Rich Man’s Roth” because there is no limit to the amount you can save toward your policy and no income cap you can make to invest. 

I’d love to help you set up your future through building equity and leaving a legacy for your family, dm me IM READY to get more info to set yourself up today!

Just because you’re limited in a certain area doesn’t mean you can’t still WORK. No excuses

Lateral Explosion & hip/glute strength 

Due to my injury history and stage 4 arthritis in me knee I’m technically not supposed to be able to do these movements. The only reason I am able to work through it is because of the exercises I learned through physical therapy with @doctor_reef over the years and my core/foundation is strong 

My foundation is my core strength, my hips, my glutes, quads, hamstrings, and calves. Each muscle is being activated and contracted on every movement throughout each video. My emphasis when I work lower body is  Lateral force from the ground and single leg balance & stability. 

There a few pointers I will give you that will help lessen/relieve knee pain while working out your lower body:

1. Find an effective static & active warm up 
2. Do a few exercises that activate your glutes, hips, and core before you start 
3. Grab a band and do some TKEs to activate your VMO in your quad 
4. When you do squats or lunges do not go below 90% until you are pain free
5. When you squat, sit back into your hips to make sure your shin angle is vertical 

Try these tips and thank me later! Let’s go!!!
